A probe into illegal permits and visas will kick off soon with Home Affairs honing in on high profile individuals. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - A committee will begin probing permits and visas, that were illegally issued since 2004. Home Affairs Minister, Aaron Motsoaledi, has emphasised they are zoning in on high-profile individuals. READ: Home Affairs welcomes Public Protector's report on Citizenship Act The minister detailed the working framework for a task team on Wednesday. eNCA's Lindokuhle Xulu shares more details in the video above.